This article discusses a series of executive orders issued by President Donald Trump on December 21, 2017. These orders are aimed at addressing the prevalence and severity of human rights abuse and corruption that originate from outside the United States. The orders block the property and interests in property of individuals and entities involved in serious human rights abuse or corruption. They also suspend the entry of certain individuals into the United States and prohibit the making of donations to blocked persons. The Secretary of the Treasury and the Secretary of State are authorized to take necessary actions to implement these orders. The article includes a list of individuals whose property and interests in property are blocked pursuant to these orders.